The paper discusses the computation and calibration of implied posterior probabilities for Support Vector Machines (SVMs) in binary classification. This topic falls under the broad area of machine learning, which is covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category as it covers the general area of machine learning, which includes SVMs. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as SVMs are a popular machine learning algorithm used in AI applications. 

cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is another possible sub-category as SVMs are commonly used in image classification tasks. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a less likely sub-category as SVMs are not typically considered neural networks, but some research has explored combining SVMs with neural networks. 

cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is even less likely as the paper does not appear to be related to social or information networks.
